requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device that alerts the LSF when the filtering system requires change or maintenance, with data retrieved via a dedicated application.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify what 'LSF' stands for, which could lead to confusion.
issues.suggested_fix: Define 'LSF' (likely 'Life Support Facility') in the requirements glossary.

issues.description: The requirement mentions a 'dedicated application' but does not specify its functionality or how it retrieves data.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the role and interface of the dedicated application.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall include a monitoring device that communicates water quality and contamination levels to the LSF.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify how the monitoring device communicates (e.g., wired, wireless, protocol).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the communication method (e.g., 'via a wired connection using Protocol X').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor the health of critical equipment via a network of wired or wireless sensors covering systems such as power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify how the sensor data is processed or where it is stored.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the data processing and storage requirements (e.g., 'Sensor data shall be stored in the facility's database and analyzed by the control system').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Support scientific data exchange with the US research lab through encrypted transmission.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify the encryption standard or protocol.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the encryption standard (e.g., 'using TLS 1.2 or higher').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The US-based Research Team shall establish cloud-based storage accessible by the facility via the World Wide Web.

issues.description: The requirement assumes internet connectivity, which may not be reliable in remote locations like Antarctica.
issues.suggested_fix: Add a fallback mechanism (e.g., 'with local caching for offline access').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall provide laundry capability.

issues.description: The requirement is vague—does 'laundry capability' refer to machines, manual washing, or both?
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify the laundry method (e.g., 'via at least one washing machine and one drying machine').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall generate a daily report on energy consumption.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify the format or storage location of the report.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify report details (e.g., 'in CSV format, stored on the server').

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall adhere to the 30-70-20 Pollution Prevention Policy.

issues.description: The requirement references '30-70-20 Pollution Prevention Policy' without defining it.
issues.suggested_fix: Define the policy or provide a reference document.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall adhere to the 30-50-75 Environmental Effects Abroad of Major Agency Actions.

issues.description: The requirement references an unclear policy ('30-50-75 Environmental Effects Abroad of Major Agency Actions').
issues.suggested_fix: Define the policy or provide a reference document.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Software and firmware updates shall not interrupt critical system functions.

issues.description: The requirement does not define 'critical system functions' or how to measure interruptions.
issues.suggested_fix: List critical systems (e.g., 'heating, water filtration') and define acceptable downtime.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Software and firmware updates shall be executed manually.

issues.description: This conflicts with REQ-075, which implies updates should not disrupt systems (manual updates may cause disruptions).
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether updates can be automated if they meet REQ-075.

domain_model_issues.description: The 'Facility' class is referenced in relationships but is not defined in the domain model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add the 'Facility' class with attributes like 'name', 'location', and methods like 'transport()'.

domain_model_issues.description: The term 'LSF' is used in requirements but not modeled as a class.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an 'LSF' class (or clarify it as an alias for 'Facility').

domain_model_issues.description: The relationship does not capture the 'dedicated application' mentioned in REQ-003.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a 'DedicatedApp' class and link it to MonitoringDevice.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks attributes/methods to address 'extreme weather conditions' (REQ-006).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'weatherResistanceRating' and methods like 'handleExtremeWeather()'.

domain_model_issues.description: The class does not reflect the smart device control capability (REQ-083, REQ-085).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add methods like 'operateViaSmartDevice()' and link to SmartDevice class.

domain_model_issues.description: The class lacks attributes/methods for fire detection (REQ-072) and CO monitoring (REQ-073).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'fireDetectionStatus' and methods like 'testFireDetection()'.

domain_model_issues.description: The class does not reflect the ability to notify occupants (REQ-062 to REQ-066).
The class does not reflect encryption requirements (REQ-047, REQ-013).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'encryptionStandard' and methods like 'encryptData()'.

domain_model_issues.description: The multiplicity is '1' for Server, but REQ-017 suggests cloud storage (multiple servers possible).
The class does not reflect water quality monitoring (REQ-005) or maintenance alerts (REQ-080).

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for monitoring device to alert about water storage levels (potable, black, gray water)
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The monitoring device shall alert the LSF when water storage levels (potable, black, gray) fall below 20% of capacity.
missing_requirements.rationale: Water storage levels are critical for operations but currently only quality monitoring is specified (REQ-005). Capacity alerts are equally important.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for handling ice core storage temperature deviations
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall automatically activate backup cooling when ice core storage temperature deviates beyond -40°F to 20°F range for more than 5 minutes, and notify the LSF.
missing_requirements.rationale: Ice core preservation is mission-critical (REQ-011), but no failure handling is defined despite the explicit temperature attribute.

missing_requirements.description: Missing security requirement for smart device authentication
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All smart devices used for facility control (REQ-083/085) shall require multi-factor authentication before granting control access.
missing_requirements.rationale: Control system security is partially addressed (REQ-077-079), but smart device access lacks authentication specifics despite critical control capabilities.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for fuel storage monitoring
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall monitor fuel levels and consumption rates, alerting the LSF when remaining fuel falls below 72 hours of projected usage.
missing_requirements.rationale: Fuel is mission-critical but only storage compliance is specified (REQ-040). Monitoring is implied by REQ-009 but not explicitly required.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for fire suppression system activation
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The fire suppression system shall automatically activate when smoke or heat thresholds are exceeded in any compartment, simultaneously notifying all occupants and McMurdo Station.
missing_requirements.rationale: System existence is noted (REQ-086) but no operational requirements are defined despite being a life-critical system.

missing_requirements.description: No data backup requirement for encrypted server
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The encrypted server shall perform incremental backups every 4 hours and full backups daily, with copies stored both locally and in the cloud (REQ-017).
missing_requirements.rationale: Data storage is specified (REQ-016/017) but backup procedures are absent despite the remote environment's high risk of data loss.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for potable water pH level alerts
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The potable water system shall alert occupants when pH levels deviate from EPA/WHO standards (REQ-058) by more than 0.5 pH units for over 15 minutes.
missing_requirements.rationale: pH display exists (REQ-087) but no thresholds or alerting logic is defined despite water quality being critical.

missing_requirements.description: No maintenance requirement for exercise/dining equipment
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All exercise and dining area equipment shall undergo weekly integrity checks, with results logged in the maintenance system.
missing_requirements.rationale: These spaces have size requirements (REQ-030/031) but no maintenance provisions despite heavy usage.

missing_requirements.description: Missing requirement for network outage handling
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: When network speeds fall below 50% of required minimums (REQ-045/046/061) for more than 5 minutes, the system shall switch to backup communication channels and notify the LSF.
missing_requirements.rationale: Network specs exist but no failure handling is defined despite critical dependence on communications.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for disposal system capacity monitoring
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The disposal system shall alert the LSF when waste storage reaches 85% capacity or when extreme weather impacts functionality (REQ-006).
missing_requirements.rationale: Disposal system weather resilience is specified but capacity monitoring is absent despite limited storage in remote environments.
